Anterior telopod (Fig. 17
B-D
): Harp carrying three stridulation ribs (Fig. 17B). Shape usual for the genus, telopoditomere 4 as long as 2 and 3 combined, with one large triangular spine and 2 or 3 smaller ones (Fig. 15C, D). Podomere 3 with one large spine juxtaposed to process of telopoditomere 2 (Fig. 17D).
